Class PalisadeInputSplit

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.hadoop.mapreduce.InputSplit
      • uk.gov.gchq.palisade.mapreduce.PalisadeInputSplit
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    org.apache.hadoop.io.Writable

    public class PalisadeInputSplit
extends org.apache.hadoop.mapreduce.InputSplit
implements org.apache.hadoop.io.Writable
    The input split for PalisadeInputFormat. This class contains all the information for describing the resources for one split and the necessary connection methods for finding the data services responsible for finding those resources.

        public PalisadeInputSplit(java.lang.String token,
                          java.util.Map<LeafResource,ConnectionDetail> resources,
                          RequestId originalRequestId)
        Create a new input split. The given details are wrapped inside a new DataRequestResponse object.
        Parameters:
        token - the token to validate that the request for data has been registered
        resources - the resources to be processed by this split
        originalRequestId - this Id is unique per data access request from a user
        Throws:
        java.lang.NullPointerException - if anything is null
